Create an Einstein Bot Block

You can create an Einstein bot block to share specific functions inside your bot with other bots. You can package bot templates and share them between orgs or on AppExchange.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:
	
Customize Application
	
OR
	
Modify Metadata
	
OR
	
Manage Bots

From the Einstein Bots main page, go to the Blocks tab. To launch the template setup flow, click New Block.
Specify your blockâ€™s name, primary language and any secondary languages, and the type of bot you want to create from your template. Optionally, you can add a permission set to your block so any bots that import your block have access to required resources.

Give a name to the first dialog in your block. All blocks must include at least one dialog.
Click Finish.
The Einstein Bot Builder opens to the new block and dialog.

Create a Block from a Dialog Group
Export a dialog group as the basis for a bot block. You can package bot blocks and share them between orgs or on AppExchange.
Package an Einstein Bot Block
Create a managed package to share your bot blocks between orgs or on AppExchange.
title: Creating Einstein Bot Blocks
